---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { APP_NAME, PUBLISHER, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../lib/constants';
---
<Base
  title={`Privacy Policy — ${APP_NAME}`}
  description={`How ${APP_NAME} handles your information. Private by design: no accounts, no ads, no analytics.`}
>
  <article class="container-x py-20 prose-chorder">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="display text-4xl sm:text-5xl mt-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-text/60 mt-3">Effective date: May 26, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-text/85 leading-relaxed text-base sm:text-lg">
      <p>
        {APP_NAME} is published by {PUBLISHER}. This Privacy Policy explains how {APP_NAME}
        handles information when you use the app.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Summary</h2>
      <p>
        {APP_NAME} is designed to work on your device. The app does not require an account, does
        not include advertising, does not include analytics, and does not send your imported
        charts, microphone audio, or app library data to {PUBLISHER} servers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Information you provide to the app</h2>
      <p>
        {APP_NAME} lets you import and manage song charts. Depending on how you use the app,
        this may include:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>PDF files or other chart files you choose to import.</li>
        <li>Song titles, artists, keys, chords, lyrics, setlists, notes, tags, and edits you create in the app.</li>
        <li>App preferences such as theme choices and display settings.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information is stored locally on your device so the app can display, search, edit, and
        organize your charts.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Microphone access</h2>
      <p>
        {APP_NAME} may request microphone access for the experimental chord detection feature.
      </p>
      <p>
        Microphone audio is processed on your device to estimate chords and beat information.
        {APP_NAME} does not record, save, upload, or share microphone audio with {PUBLISHER}. You
        can deny microphone permission or stop chord detection at any time.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">On-device processing</h2>
      <p>
        {APP_NAME} uses on-device processing for features such as PDF import, OCR fallback for
        scanned charts, chord parsing, Nashville number conversion, transposition, capo display,
        and chord detection.
      </p>
      <p>
        The app does not use these features to transmit your chart contents or audio to {PUBLISHER}.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Information shared with third parties</h2>
      <p>
        {APP_NAME} does not sell your information and does not share your imported charts, app
        library, notes, or microphone audio with third parties.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some app functionality uses Android platform services and libraries on your device, such as
        file picking, local storage, and on-device text recognition. Your use of Google Play and
        Android device services is also subject to Google’s privacy policies and your device
        settings.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Device backup and transfer</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your Android device settings, app data may be included in Android backup or
        device-to-device transfer features provided by the operating system. {PUBLISHER} does not
        control those Android backup services.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Data retention and deletion</h2>
      <p>
        Your app data remains on your device until you delete it in the app, clear the app’s data,
        uninstall the app, or remove files using Android system tools.
      </p>
      <p>To delete {APP_NAME} data, you can:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>Delete songs, setlists, notes, tags, or imported charts in the app where supported.</li>
        <li>Use Android Settings to clear {APP_NAME}’s app data.</li>
        <li>Uninstall {APP_NAME} from your device.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Children’s privacy</h2>
      <p>
        {APP_NAME} is not directed to children under 13. The app does not knowingly collect
        personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        {PUBLISHER} may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted with
        a new effective date.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, contact {PUBLISHER} at
        <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`} class="text-accent hover:underline">{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
